history.content:
Yes, in general they allow you to petition up to 2 classes to count as upper div units. 

However, that being said, seems like you're a freshman/sophomore. Have you taken EE 123 yet? I personally think that taking digital image processing without digital signal processing is a bit like taking math 53 before math 1b. One of them is simply a 2D application of the other, and the former makes little to no sense without the latter.

children.subject:
I would say to just go with EE 123 (or maybe just 120) if it fits in you're schedule. If you're only prep is 16AB, based off the syllabus you're gonna have a really rough time.

DIP is deeply deeply rooted in signals.

If you pay attention in lecture for 225B and have good programming skills, you can easily do well in 225B. I took it without 120 (only 16AB) and did very well. Just write good reviews of the readings and start early on the project and homeworks and an A is very doable.

I am actually a senior student. The professor said EE16AB series will suffice as basic prep work but made it clear that is not an easy class. Someone recommended me to take a signal processing class alongside.
